cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.BIO. 

The paper involves medical imaging and robotics for cochlear implant surgery, which suggests it could fall under cs.MED or cs.RO. The use of OCT for enhanced imaging suggests it could also fall under cs.CV or cs.MM. The mention of automated segmentation and comparison to ground truth suggests it could also fall under cs.BIO.
